texts.text:
At long last... At long last,
my revival is close at hand.

Countless years, I have awaited
this moment.
But it will not be long now.

It is time, "God." You will pay
for my persecution, obscurity.

When you are banished,
I will be the one true God.

So, this is the Aura Gate
Hikaru came to.
Well, Seiran? Sense anything?
Let me see.
No trace of him yet.

But I can tell this entrance was
formed recently.

The energy of this Aura Gate is
different from the ones we know.
What, you can tell? Whoa.

Yo, in cases like these, there's
usually a special demon at work.
Hikaru is a Dx2.

He might have gone inside
knowing demons were involved.
So, he really is here?

Wait, no. I just said he might
be here. Might.

I'm so glad I decided to ask the
Tokyo Liberators!

Let's hurry and get in there!
How do you enter?

Hey, hey, hey! You don't think
you're actually comin' with us?
This is a veritable demon nest.

For someone as untrained as you,
venturing inside is suicide.
Do you have a death wish?

No way! That's why I asked you
Dx2 for help.
Er, yeah, I get that, but...

Plus, I think you guys are
really underestimating Hikaru!
He's, like, super stubborn!

You saying it's dangerous isn't
gonna stop him now.

He's not coming back home unless
I go in there and drag him out.
I get that, but...

Don't bother trying to stop me.
I already decided I'm going.

Seems like neither of you twins
listen to what you're told.
You say something?
Nope!

I am also a bit nervous about
bringing her along.

However, she is very
well-informed about us Dx2.
Yup, that's right.

I've heard much more than I ever
wanted to. I know the deal.

We're up against real demons.
Begging for mercy won't work.

I'm prepared for the worst.
Can I still not come?
Akari...

Honestly, I can't bring myself
to stop her.

I am well aware what she
suggests is reckless.

But she's worried about her Dx2
brother. I suppose I can relate.
Rika... Yeah, I get it.

Megakin, could I ask you to let
Akari come along?
I pledge to keep her safe.
Whoa... That's so cool.

It won't do to bear that burden
alone, Rika. I'll join you.
So cool!

Geez. Y'all are makin' it real
hard to say no.
So, I won't. Let's go together.

But if I say it's too sketchy,
you get out. No matter what.
That cool with you?

Totally! Totally! Don't wanna be
in there too long anyway!

Let's go grab the big dummy and
go home!

>Akari and the Liberators head
inside the Aura Gate.

Whoa. This is an Aura Gate?
Weird vibe.

I can't believe there's a place
like this underneath Tokyo.

Quite different from everything
aboveground, no?

Yeah. Hikaru talked about demons
but I only half believed him.

Coming here is making it all
start to feel real.
Well, you are a civilian.

Most would find this world hard
to believe from talk alone.

So, can you tell us
what Hikaru looks—
There he is!
What?
>Akari dashes forward.

>She's headed for a young man
fighting alone against a demon!
This is the end!
*Roars*

>Felled by Hikaru's attack,
the demon begins to vanish.

Why? Why do you insist on
killing us? Why us?

Reborn, only to be slain.
Then reborn again...
>The demon vanishes.

Phew. How many does that make?
Well, off to find the next one.
Hikaru!
Huh? Akari?

>Akari all but tackles Hikaru
when she sprints up.

What the hell are you doing
out here?!
Mama and Papa are worried sick!

Quit hunting demons, slackass,
and get yourself home!
Me? Quit being so selfish!
Oh, so I'm being selfish?

Oh, please! Since when do you
think about anyone but yourself?

You'd never understand what I'm
trying to do here!
Just leave me alone!

Hold it, hold it! What good'll
it do for y'all to fight here?

>The Liberators catch up. At
their arrival, Hikaru frowns.

Akari, what are you and these
other civilians even doing here?

These people are Dx2! They're
from the Tokyo branch!

I asked them to find you because
you weren't coming back!

Dx2? Perfect. Take her and get
out, if you wouldn't mind.

It's dangerous. Akari needs to
leave before she gets hurt.
But what about y—

I got unfinished business. I'm
counting on you. Get her out.
H-Hey, wait!

>Hikaru runs off, disappearing
into a gate.
He's moving to the next floor!
He's not getting away! Wait up!

Hey! Hey! Great, now she's
getting away!
We're going after them, y'all!

>Everyone follows Akari, jumping
one after another into the gate.
>And thenー
Owww.

What happened? It felt like I
got bounced back right before...
Akari. Seiran. Are you two okay?

Yes, somehow. You seem fine
as well, Rika.

In any case, what do we do now?
I don't see the boys at all.

But how come? Did we get sent to
a different place?
No.

Not a different place. I believe
we were not permitted entry.
This is the same floor.

There is a chance only the boys
moved on to the next floor.

What? Is this Hikaru's way of
telling me I can't come?

Dammit Hikaru! You can't just
treat family like this!

I-I doubt he can manipulate the
structure of this Aura Gate.

There's a chance the boys were
repelled and scattered, too.
Just hang on a moment. Please?
Ugh.

Having to proceed separately is
an unexpected development.

But in any case, Megakin and the
others will chase down Hikaru.
Let's work to link up with them.
